                            <comment id="246666" author="jamesanunez" created="Fri, 3 May 2019 18:32:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We are still seeing sanityn test 101a fail with &apos;Found WRITE RPC but expect none&apos; for master 2.12.53.1; &lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/d3fd6ad0-6dc2-11e9-a6f9-52540065bddc&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/d3fd6ad0-6dc2-11e9-a6f9-52540065bddc&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m not sure if &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-11752&quot; title=&quot;sanity test 271f fails with &amp;#39;1 READ RPC occured&amp;#39;&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-11752&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-11752&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; should be reopened instead of this one. This failure is for SLES ldiskfs, not ZFS. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
